Variable names seen as keywords in C+

`abstract`, `local` and `initonly` are no C / C++  keywords but the types of the variables would be shown as names.
This is easily shown by an example like:
```
/*! \brief brief */
int local = 42;
/*! \brief brief */
float initonly = 42;
/*! \brief brief */
double abstract = 42;
/*! \brief brief */
int local0 = 7;
```
